    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-25T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="988"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d988">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163 Am 3/641: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsinan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsinan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-26T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 26, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 3—6:24
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my despatch No. 322 of March 11,<note n="78" xml:id="d988fn1">Not
                        found in Department files.</note> third paragraph, Catholic Bishop of Tsinan
                    was yesterday assured by senior Japanese <pb facs="0912" n="902" xml:id="pg_902"
                    /> general here, upon approaching the latter concerning the question, that
                    American Catholic missionaries would not be interned and would be permitted to
                    continue their work in the event of war between the United States and Japan.</p>
                <p>By mail to Peiping in code. Sent to the Department, repeated to Chungking. Code
                    text by air mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
